<font color="#FF0000">HAM AND LIMA BEANS FOR DINNER</font><br>
<tt>Wed Dec 10 20:09:26 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I never did like Ham and Lima beans but I eat them in Nam because they filled me up. <br>
Now I can choose if I want to go to Taco Bell or McDonalds for a fine meal.<br><br>
But it isn't until I get home to sit around the family table where I can truly enjoy a  meal. Is it because of the food being served or the company sitting around the table? <br><br>
Their were no great cathedrals in early Christianity, they weren't built until about the year 300 AD, no one in authority was dictating what or who is suppose to do what. <br><br>
The church trusted in God and not men. That little band of illiterates the Lord left behind had managed to give us a wealth of personal encounters and experiences with God that changed religious beliefs and turned the world upside down. <br><br>
They were in the beginning spat upon, humiliated, and called all kinds of names and subjected to great harm. Sill they prevailed with only the Apostle John escaping martyrdom. <br><br>
Gosh we need that type of simple preaching once again, by individuals that are not afraid to say what is in their hearts without fear of offending someone. <br><br>
Then it really wouldn’t matter what we ate, it would be the company at the table that would draw us together, because we would know they love their God by the life they lead and that would be nice. 
